I’ve been blessed to see yet another year 🙏🏾✨ A new season! I thank God and give Him all of the glory for everything….the past few decades have been such a journey….one written by the best….God Himself…and this testimony I have to share is something different…totally unique to me and my situation….the good and the bad….and I’m grateful for it all….it’s cultivated me into the woman I am….proud to be…and I’m looking forward to see who I continue to grow into….it took a long time for me to get here…to this level of understanding….and trust me…there are levels to this…I wasn’t capable of imagining this life for myself….at times I didn’t even think that I deserved it…sometimes I’m still in disbelief….but knowing that this is exactly what it’s supposed to be….and living to the fullest in that….is yet another triumph….and I’m getting better at it every single day….I plan on knocking down every single door that has my name on it….and standing in the doorway like I own it! Because God said this is what He’s planned for me….no matter who or what tries to say otherwise…ain’t nothing gonna get in the way….NOTHING!!! Everyone may not agree with the route….but it’s mine!!!! Period!!! I thank each and every single person that has genuinely been there and supported me….not just professionally…but personally….if you know me for real…you know that real life weighs more in my book….and if you’ve been here with me….you know who you are….and I love you! And thank you from the bottom of my heart ❤️ This birthday just feels a little different for me this year….almost like the beginning of my greatness….we’ve already been doing great things….but it’s time to exude all of the greatness in me 🙏🏾✨ Here’s to 32 🥂

Do you know what it feels like to be lost in the depths of emotions, struggling to stay afloat? 💔💭 I’ve been there a few times in this life; especially in this song. I can’t speak for everyone, but when I am drowning, I like to submerge myself in my work. It tends to be the best time for me to be creative. So, I completely put myself out there and was a part of the entire process with this record. From involving my producing team to create a fire ass canvas for me to paint the words of my heart on, to writing the video treatment and putting each piece of the puzzle together to create an even bigger and more dynamic picture. I explored the depths of my vulnerability while unveiling the hidden struggles that were silently consuming me at the time…and the way that everything came together to help me manifest the vision….I’m forever grateful to God and every single person that played a position in making it happen 🙏🏾✨

YNVS C.E.O. JUAN “SHAMPOO” RAMIREZ INKS NEW DISTRIBUTION DEAL FOR YNVS MUSIC GROUP WITH UMG (UNIVERSAL MUSIC GROUP)/VARICK ST./DEF JAM 🔥🔥🔥🔥

CEO of YNVS Music Group and music industry veteran, Juan “Shampoo” Ramirez, announces a significant achievement securing a new distribution deal with UMG/VARICK ST./DEF JAM. This marks a remarkable milestone in his longstanding career within the music industry and his dedication to various projects with top artists speaks volumes about his impact. 

“This is full circle…it’s been a long time coming…and it hasn’t been easy for me…it’s been a long grind.”, says Ramirez. “Staying connected to the streets and the youth is crucial for continued success and longevity.” 

Shampoo has been an independent contractor with Def Jam for over 14 years and has handled promotional and marketing campaigns for some of your favorite artists such as Jay-z, N.O.R.E., Busta Rhymes, Rick Ross, Ye, Ne-yo, Fabolous, Jadakiss, and so much more. Shampoo’s extensive experience as an independent contractor with Def Jam, Epic, Capitol, Republic, etc and his involvement developing artists’ projects with world-renowned artists showcase his impact. 

Universal Music Group Executive Noah Sheer ( @noahsheer ) says, “We are proud to partner with Shampoo, who has an extensive history in the music industry making great strides. This venture between UMG with YNVS is a testament to his commitment and perseverance in the industry.” 

The first artist due to drop in February 2024 is Brooke Lynne ( @ynvsbrookelynne ) featuring the single release “Rubbaband Gal” on UMG/VARICKST/DEF JAM. The label will drop releases from new artists Conan ( @ynvsconan ), Tony Notez ( @ynvstony ), Babyfvc Eli ( @babyfvce_eli ), and veteran rapper, Mic Geronimo ( @micgeronimo ). Thank you @epmd11 🙏🏾✨
